value.0: Hello once again, surfacer. Is there something you need?

I guess I could answer a few questions for you. Can't see any harm in it. Besides, it's not like the Maker's golems here on the island will tell you anything. <StartAction>[She smiles briefly at her own joke.]</Start>
Well, the island was named after the ancient duergar mage who built his stronghold here centuries ago. They say the Maker came here so he could work in peace while perfecting his golems.
There must be some truth to these stories. There's some ruins to the north that could have been the Maker's laboratory, though all that's left is the dungeon. And there's the golems, of course.
The dungeon at the north end of the island is crawling with golems. At least, the first floor of it is. We don't go any deeper. We figure they're guardians left over from the Maker.

They must have been built to protect against thieves and scavengers.<StartAction> [She gives you a rueful look.] </Start>They do a pretty good job, too. We've lost more than a few duergar during our expeditions.
<StartAction>[She shakes her head.]</Start> Not possible. There's some kind of scavenger golem in there that repairs and rebuilds any golems we manage to take down.
We've tried to kill the scavenger, but it's got a number of magical defenses. Every time we attack it, it teleports away to safety. That damn thing makes our job a lot tougher.
Everything I know about the Maker comes from legends and myths. They say he was a powerful duergar sorcerer who isolated himself on this island to work on his research.
His specialty was crafting golems. According to the legends, he found a way to imbue his constructs with intelligence and free will. But the golems we've run into seem pretty standard to me.
Nobody really knows; he disappeared five centuries ago. Most people think he was killed off by his own creations: intelligent golems with a will of their own.
I don't know if I really believe that, but it makes a good story. The only golems we've run across in the dungeon don't seem all that smart to me. Damn tough to kill, though.

<StartAction>[This duergar female looks you up and down, gauging your strength and trying to judge if you are a threat. Satisfied that you pose no immediate harm, she seems to relax slightly.]</Start>
Not many come to this island, especially not a surfacer like you. What are you doing here? Have you come as friend or foe?
<StartAction>[The duergar raise their weapons, but at a signal from their leader they hold their ground. She gives you a quick once over, evaluating you as a potential threat.]</Start>
If this is a joke, you picked the wrong group to play games with. We're not looking for a fight, but we're well armed and we will defend ourselves.
You should've picked an easier target! Attack!
<StartAction>[She nods.]</Start> Fair enough. As long as you aren't here to cause trouble for us, you can keep your secrets. My name is Dahanna. I'm the leader of this expedition.
<StartAction>[The duergar visibly relaxes, though she is still studying you carefully as she addresses you once more.]</Start> My name is Dahanna. I'm the leader of this expedition.
Come and go as you please, surfacer. You don't answer to us.
<StartAction>[She nods thoughtfully.]</Start> The Valsharess. I've heard about her. One of the drow matron mothers, isn't she? She's made quite a name for herself recently.
I hear she's been attacking the surface... I guess that's why you're looking to stop her. But you won't find any help against her here. If the drow don't bother us, we don't bother them.
<StartCheck>[Failure] Dahanna shakes her head slowly. </Start>I don't want trouble with you, surfacer. But you bullying us won't make us join you. Our minds are set; you can't change them.
<StartCheck>[Failure] Dahanna shrugs. </Start>Maybe. But the Valsharess isn't the first drow we've seen rise to power. Most of them get toppled long before they ever turn their attention to us.
We're treasure hunters. Centuries ago, this island was home to a powerful duergar wizard known as the Maker, or so the stories go. The Maker's long gone, but he left a few things behind.
We come out here to salvage rare metal and pieces of golems from the ruins of the Maker's tower. You'd be surprised what the right buyer will pay for an arm made of pure adamantine.

<StartAction>[She grins.]</Start> But it isn't easy. Not too many expeditions come here anymore. There's still some good metal to be found, but you have to be willing to go toe-to-toe with the Maker's golems.
As usual, the duergar are scavengers, living off the scraps of others.
Better watch your tongue, drow! This is duergar territory. Your arrogance might have cost you more than you're willing to pay.

<StartAction>[Dahanna and the other duergar approach you. You notice their weapons are drawn and that they have packed up their camp. Dahanna appears uncomfortable, as if she is ashamed of what is about to happen.]</Start>
You were in that dungeon an awfully long time. It gave me a chance to talk things over with my crew. We've decided we don't much like someone else moving in on our island.
We've been working this island for nearly twenty years. We've paid our dues in sweat and blood, and we've defended our claim against all comers. It's nothing personal, surfacer.
We need that salvage from the Maker's lab to earn our living. We can't just let you walk off with your pick of the best stuff. We were here first, by rights we deserve a share of anything you found!
If you give us 10,000 gold pieces, we'll let you go on your way without any trouble. If not, we'll take what's rightfully ours by force.
<StartAction>[Failure] [Dahanna smiles.] </Start>Your <race> lies don't fool me. You were in there far too long to come out empty handed. Now, give us what's rightfully ours.
<StartAction>[Success] [Dahanna cocks her head to the side, considering your words.]</Start> You seem sincere. I can't say for sure whether you're lying or not.
<StartAction>[Failure]</Start> We've held our own against the Maker's golems. I think we can manage against a <race> surfacer like you. We'll fight for what is rightfully ours.
<StartAction>[Success] [Dahanna studies you closely, then seems to come to a decision.]</Start> You're probably right, surfacer. We're not willing to throw our lives away.
You've gone deeper into the Maker's dungeon than we ever did, and you've come back to tell the tale. We'd be foolish to go up against you, even as desperate as we are.
<StartAction>[Failure]</Start> We've been working this island for twenty years, and we've lost our fair share of duergar. We've paid our dues... you owe us something!

<StartAction>[Success]</Start> Maybe... maybe you're right, surfacer. We aren't thieves, we earn our living honestly. <StartAction>[There is some angry grumbling from the soldiers, but Dahanna cuts them off with a single gesture.]</Start>

<StartAction>[The leader of the duergar shakes her head.]</Start> I'm sorry for this. But  we count on these expeditions to survive. Each time we come back, we find less and less good metal. We are growing desperate.

<StartAction>[Dahanna looks at you with obvious disbelief, though she takes the offered coins.]</Start> You would do this for us, after what just happened? You are more forgiving than we duergar, surfacer.
<StartAction>[She smiles.]</Start> Thank you for this gift. Our expedition here is over now, we're heading back to our homes and our families. It will be nice to return with a few extra coins.
Our expedition here is over now, surfacer. We're heading back to our homes and our families.
I can't honestly say whether we will come back to this island again. In any case, we wish you luck, surfacer. Remember: the Underdark is a dangerous place.
<StartAction>[She nods.]</Start> Maybe you're right. Perhaps the rewards here are no longer worth the risks. There are other places we can go, places far less dangerous than this island.
<StartAction>[Failure]</Start> <StartAction>[Dahanna considers your counter offer carefully, calculating the chances of her group against you. Finally she shakes her head.]</Start>
One thousand gold won't go very far, split between all of us. I think we've earned the right to at least 10,000, considering you're poaching our claim here.
<StartAction>[Dahanna sighs.] </Start>I was hoping it wouldn't come to this, but I can see you aren't being reasonable. Attack!
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> <StartAction>[Dahanna considers your counter offer carefully, calculating the chances of her group against you. Finally, she nods in acceptance.] </Start>
<StartAction>[The soldiers behind Dahanna begin to murmur excitedly, but she cuts them off with a sharp hand gesture. She takes the offered coins.]</Start> I'm glad this was done without bloodshed.
A polite thief is still a thief. Being courteous doesn't make this right.
Well, at least you is polite... for a thief.
Well, at least you're being courteous while you rob us. That's more than I expected from your kind.
<StartAction>[Nathyrra spits on the ground.]</Start> You would bargain with this hargluk?
<StartAction>[Dahanna ignores her.]</Start> If you give us 10,000 gold pieces, we'll let you go on your way without any trouble. If not, we'll take what's rightfully ours by force.
Nothing personal? That's funny. When a pack of armed thugs points their weapons at me, I tend to take it *very* personally.
Look, Boss! Them duergar is coming to give us a welcome back surprise party... uh, wait. Deekin not thinks this a party after all. Too bad. Deekin wants cake.
I want to ask you some questions.
Tell me more about the island.
Tell me about the golems.
I would've thought you'd cleared all the golems out by now.
Tell me about the Maker.
What happened to him?
Friend or foe? Uh... I guess I'll pick foe!
<StartHighlight>[Evil]</Start> It's no joke. I just want to slaughter you all. I'm funny that way.
Calm down. I'm not looking for a fight, either.
My name and business are my own.
My name is <FullName>. I don't mean any harm.
I'll be going now.
<StartHighlight>[Evil]</Start>Time for this to get bloody. Die, you Underdark excuse for a dwarf!
I'm looking for allies to help me against the Valsharess.
<StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> You're either with me or against me. Think about it.
<StartHighlight>[Evil]</Start> I gave you a chance. Now you'll pay the price! <StartAction>[Attack]</Start>
Fine. I want to ask you something else then.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Eventually the Valsharess will turn her army against the duergar, too.
What are you doing here?
I have some other questions.
Relax. We'll just be going now.
Settle down. We just want to ask you some questions.
Nobody threatens me! Death to the duergar! <StartAction>[Attack]</Start>
Is this some kind of shake down?
Your island? What are you talking about?
I think I see where this is going...
Maybe we could work out a deal.
<StartAction>[Bluff]</Start> I didn't find anything worthwhile. You've picked this place clean.
<StartAction>[Intimidate]</Start> Careful now. This may be more than you can handle.
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> You have no right to my stuff. I did all the work!
Apology *not* accepted! You'll pay for this with blood!
<StartHighlight>[Good]</Start> Sounds like times are tough. Here's a thousand gold to help you out.
That's okay. There's no hard feelings.
Maybe it's time you moved on to somewhere else.
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> I'll give you a thousand gold... no more.
